    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what I found and what the plan does:\n\n### Codebase Analysis\n\n- `common/chat.cpp` contains 7 existing specialized handlers (Ministral 3, GPT-OSS, Functionary v3.2, Kimi K2, LFM2, LFM2.5, GigaChatV3) — all following an identical pattern\n- `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (line 1634) detects templates by scanning marker strings in the Jinja source, dispatching to handlers in order, returning `std::nullopt` if none match\n- `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists in `chat.h` — **no header changes needed**\n- `using json = nlohmann::ordered_json` is already aliased at line 31\n\n### The Plan (2 changes to `common/chat.cpp` only)\n\n**1. New handler function** (insert at line 1518, after GigaChatV3 handler):\n- Iterates `inputs.messages` using `msg.value(\"role\",\"\")` / `msg.value(\"content\",\"\")`\n- Saves system message, prepends it to first user turn with `\\n` separator\n- Wraps user turns in `[INST] … [/INST]`, prefixes the sequence with `<s>` once\n- Appends assistant turns as ` {content}</s>`\n- Sets `data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY`\n\n**2. Detection block** (insert at line 1689, before `return std::nullopt`):\n- Matches `[INST]` + `[/INST]` present AND `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent\n- Logs `\"Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\\n\"` via `LOG_DBG`\n- The Ministral 3 check runs first (lines 1640–1644) so there's no ambiguity, but the `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` exclusion adds extra safety",
